Program: Outlook
Title: The Day the Music Stopped
Link: https://www.bbc.co.uk/programmes/p04yzt2l
Last Broadcast Date: Tue 18 Apr 2017
Violin virtuoso Min Kym was a child prodigy whose family moved from South Korea to London to help her to develop her talent. Then, at 21, she met the love of her life: a Stradivarius violin. However, when she was at the height of her career, she became the victim of a crime that made headlines around the world. (Photo: Min Kym with her Stradivarius violin courtesy of Min Kym) Show less